data.title: Middlesex Water Co. reported Q3 2025 earnings of $0.77/share & invested $72M in infrastructure. Declared $0.36 common stock dividend.
data.description: Middlesex Water Company announced financial results for Q3 2025 with $54.1 million in operating revenues, a $1.0 million decrease compared to the previous year. Diluted EPS was $0.77, a decrease from $0.80 in Q3 2024. Net income for the nine months ending Sept 30, 2025, was $34.2 million, down $1.3 million from the same period in 2024. The company invested $72 million in water infrastructure in 2025, or 77% of the planned $93 million budget. Middlesex acquired Pinewood Acres water utility assets in Delaware. A $0.36 common stock cash dividend was declared, a 5.88% increase. The fourth quarter dividend will be payable on December 1, 2025. Middlesex has paid dividends since 1912 and this marks its 53rd consecutive year of dividend increases.

data.title: Comcast faces downgrades amid broadband challenges, as analysts downgrade with price targets cut. Goldman Sach's price target down to $30.
data.description: Comcast Corporation (NASDAQ: CMCSA) is facing difficulties in its broadband sector, leading analysts to downgrade their ratings and express concerns about pricing and investment pressures. Following the release of positive third-quarter results, key analyst takeaways include Goldman Sachs' Michael Ng downgrading the rating from Buy to Neutral and lowering the price target from $39 to $30, while KeyBanc Capital Markets' Brandon Nispel downgraded from Overweight to Sector Weight. Seaport Research Partners' David Joyce also downgraded from Buy to Neutral, and BofA Securities' Jessica Reif Ehrlich maintained a Neutral rating but reduced the price target from $36 to $31. Ng highlighted unexpected challenges in Comcast's broadband operations, with a projected 4% year-on-year decline in Connectivity & Platforms EBITDA over the next few quarters. This reflects a sequential decline in domestic broadband average revenue per user.
